stop with writing a sentence.

01:04:07.310 --> 01:04:11.060
You -- the labor comes
actually after that point.

01:04:11.060 --> 01:04:12.360
&gt;&gt; Mario Vargas Llosa: Absolutely.

01:04:12.360 --> 01:04:18.310 position:56%
I think that is the example of
Flaubert, which is very encouraging.

01:04:18.310 --> 01:04:26.570
I think you discover with Flaubert
something extremely important.

01:04:26.570 --> 01:04:34.960
If you are not born genius-- if
you are born a genius, no problem.

01:04:34.960 --> 01:04:39.630
But when you discover
that you are not a genius,

01:04:39.630 --> 01:04:43.940
this can be very discouraging for a
writer, if you want to be a writer.

01:04:43.940 --> 01:04:46.520 position:56%
Well, that was the case of Flaubert.

01:04:46.520 --> 01:04:48.130
Flaubert was not a genius.

01:04:48.130 --> 01:04:51.410
Flaubert started writing
very bad things.

01:04:51.410 --> 01:04:57.970
You know? Imitations of the
fashionable writers of his time.

01:04:57.970 --> 01:05:02.250
But he wanted to be a
great writer and he decided

01:05:02.250 --> 01:05:04.990 position:56%
that he would become a great writer.

01:05:04.990 --> 01:05:11.710
And as he was not a genius, he
decided to replace, you know,

01:05:11.710 --> 01:05:18.050
this natural force of
creativity with hard work.

01:05:18.050 --> 01:05:21.640
And this was for me
extremely important.

01:05:21.640 --> 01:05:31.790
As important as to discover
that realism could be a kind

01:05:31.790 --> 01:05:39.420
of literature that at the
same time was extremely formal

01:05:39.420 --> 01:05:44.750
with great preoccupation for the
techniques and for the language.

01:05:44.750 --> 01:05:59.070 position:56%
The way in which Flaubert built his
talent, working with such obstinacy,

01:05:59.070 --> 01:06:13.470 position:56%
with such perseverance, and imposing
himself kind of seclusion, you know,

01:06:13.470 --> 01:06:18.130
for months and for years,
is something extraordinary.

01:06:18.130 --> 01:06:20.880
And he became a very great,

01:06:20.880 --> 01:06:25.870
great writer without
being a natural genius.

01:06:25.870 --> 01:06:32.650
And that, I think, is a great
example that Flaubert gave us

01:06:32.650 --> 01:06:35.380
to the writers that we
are not born genius.

01:06:35.380 --> 01:06:41.850
You know? That working very
hard, being extremely self-critic

01:06:41.850 --> 01:06:51.430
of what you do, being
obsessed with the idea

01:06:51.430 --> 01:07:00.650 position:56%
of improve what you have done, you
can really produce great literature.

01:07:00.650 --> 01:07:03.620
And I think this is a
fantastic example, you know.

01:07:03.620 --> 01:07:07.610
The case of Rimbaud, for
example, is the opposite.

01:07:07.610 --> 01:07:12.450
Rimbaud, when he was 14 years
